http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#lab.@value: ISO 639-1: Codes for the Representation of Names of Languages - Part 1: Two-letter codes for languages

http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.@value: ISO 639-1 is the first part of the ISO 639 international-standard language-code family.                         ISO 639-1 provides two-character lowercase alphabetic strings that serve as identifiers of languages.                          The list contains approximately 180 discrete codes.                          All ISO 639-1 languages also have ISO 639-2 three-character code representations.                           These codes are linked to codes for the same languages in ISO 639-2 and the MARC Language Codes.
